N:agent-evaluation
D:Design evaluation systems for AI agents by choosing grader mix, benchmark shape, harness boundaries, and production feedback loops. Use when the user needs eval planning for coding, research, conversational, or computer-use agents, not when they simply need the feature fixed.
G:agent-evaluation evals benchmark grader harness regression suite quality monitoring red-team online evals
U[5]:
  Need an eval plan for a coding, research, conversational, or computer-use agent
  Need to choose code-based, model-based, or human graders
  Need an offline benchmark, regression gate, or launch-readiness eval packet
  Need CI or production monitoring logic for agent quality
  Need to diagnose saturation, drift, or benchmark gaming
S[6]{n,action,details}:
  1,Classify surface,Capture agent_type·decision_to_make·primary_risk·environment·available evidence·constraints
  2,Choose grader stack,Pick code-based vs model-based vs human review with a named primary grader and escalation path
  3,Design suite,Define task families·positive/negative/edge balance·success dimensions·benchmark sources
  4,Define harness,Specify environment·reset strategy·timeouts·transcript capture·PR-vs-nightly lanes
  5,Add operations,State production sampling·alert thresholds·human review path·saturation or drift checks
  6,Return packet,Produce one structured Agent Evaluation Plan with immediate next steps
R[6]:
  Start from the decision the eval must support
  Prefer outcome checks over path-matching
  Use transcript review for debugging and recalibration
  Separate deterministic PR checks from slower scheduled lanes
  Promote real incidents into frozen regression tasks
  Route feature implementation or flaky-suite repair to other skills
E[4]{desc,in,out}:
  "Coding agent gate","Design an eval plan for a coding agent that edits a repo and should only ship changes when tests and builds pass","Coding-agent evaluation plan with code-based grading, build-test gates, transcript capture, and CI-vs-nightly split"
  "Research grounding","How should we evaluate a research agent that writes sourced briefs before launch?","Research-agent evaluation plan with grounding, coverage, source quality, and verification dimensions"
  "Support chatbot monitoring","Set up a benchmark and monitoring approach for a support chatbot where empathy matters and escalation handling must stay reliable","Conversational-agent evaluation plan with structured rubric, escalation metrics, production sampling, and calibration path"
  "Boundary check","Our flaky pytest suite needs to be fixed. Can agent-evaluation handle that?","Routes repair work to backend-testing or debugging instead of pretending an eval plan alone fixes the suite"
